The paper deals with MMSE estimation of block sparse signals in compressive sensing, which involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), matrix methods (cs.MM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of the replica method from statistical physics, which is a technique commonly used in the study of disordered systems and can be classified under cs.DS (disordered systems). However, since the focus of the paper is on compressive sensing and signal processing, we consider cs.IT and cs.SP to be the most likely categories, followed by cs.MM, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
